1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.kissasia.net Support Admin)

2
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,661
[rock music playing]

3
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:44,441
[breathing heavily]

4
00:00:44,525 --> 00:00:45,526
Eui-ju!

5
00:00:45,609 --> 00:00:46,944
CHAPTER 26:
YOU'RE AN OUTLIER

6
00:00:47,027 --> 00:00:49,113
Damn it! [grunts]

7
00:00:51,365 --> 00:00:52,575
[Eui-ju groaning]

8
00:00:54,994 --> 00:00:56,412
[doctor] Hi there. How are you doing?

9
00:00:57,246 --> 00:00:59,290
-[nurse] Who's the patient's guardian?
-Yes, that's me.

10
00:00:59,373 --> 00:01:01,625
And how long has the patient
been sweating?

11
00:01:01,709 --> 00:01:02,710
About 30 minutes.

12
00:01:02,793 --> 00:01:04,295
Does the patient have a history
of stomach pain?

13
00:01:04,378 --> 00:01:07,089
-I'm sorry. I don't know.
-Okay, you don't know.

14
00:01:07,172 --> 00:01:09,300
Please go ahead
and wait in the waiting room.

15
00:01:09,383 --> 00:01:10,384
Well, is it serious?

16
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:11,677
-Please just wait out there.
-Okay.

17
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:13,596
Okay, we have an emergency!

18
00:01:13,679 --> 00:01:15,139
Okay. Let's check your stomach.

19
00:01:15,222 --> 00:01:16,515
-It hurts. Yeah.
-It hurts?

20
00:01:16,599 --> 00:01:18,267
-Let me press here this time.
-It really hurts.

21
00:01:18,350 --> 00:01:20,102
Let's transfer her to the ER now.

22
00:01:20,185 --> 00:01:21,562
We're transferring her to the ER.

23
00:01:21,645 --> 00:01:23,105
EMERGENCY ROOM
ENTRY RESTRICTIONS

24
00:01:23,188 --> 00:01:24,398
We're moving her now.

25
00:01:24,481 --> 00:01:26,692
[tense music playing]

26
00:01:36,243 --> 00:01:37,286
[breathes heavily]

27
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:46,629
Oh, boy. If they're taking her there,
it's one of two things.

28
00:01:47,254 --> 00:01:48,505
This is not good.

29
00:01:49,173 --> 00:01:50,299
Not good at all.

30
00:01:50,382 --> 00:01:51,592
[clicks tongue]

31
00:01:51,675 --> 00:01:52,676
It's not good?

32
00:01:53,177 --> 00:01:55,137
HANA UNIVERSITY MEDICAL CENTER

33
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:57,014
She's going to be okay, right?

34
00:02:07,441 --> 00:02:08,442
Well…

35
00:02:24,917 --> 00:02:26,585
[nurse] Is Yeo Eui-ju's guardian here?

36
00:02:27,544 --> 00:02:28,712
Yes, here.

37
00:02:40,724 --> 00:02:41,725
Mr. Ga.

38
00:02:42,768 --> 00:02:44,770
Mr. Ga, what do I do?

39
00:02:44,853 --> 00:02:48,607
[sobbing] I knew something was off.

40
00:02:48,691 --> 00:02:51,068
I haven't had an appetite,
and my stomach's been acting up.

41
00:02:52,277 --> 00:02:54,530
I saw this on TV recently.

42
00:02:54,613 --> 00:02:55,698
Acute leukemia.

43
00:02:56,657 --> 00:02:59,326
The program said that
even healthy people can get it.

44
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:03,664
And if you collapse out of nowhere,
it means it's already late-stage.

45
00:03:04,665 --> 00:03:05,582
I'm only…

46
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:08,627
[sobbing] I'm only 18 years old.

47
00:03:08,711 --> 00:03:13,590
I was gonna start
buying R-rated novels myself,

48
00:03:13,674 --> 00:03:17,344
load up like $70 in credits
and just binge.

49
00:03:17,428 --> 00:03:18,762
[sobbing continues]

50
00:03:19,346 --> 00:03:21,557
-Mr. Ga.
-[Woo-su sighs]

51
00:03:22,057 --> 00:03:23,058
I…

52
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:26,979
I don't have a good feeling about this.

53
00:03:27,604 --> 00:03:29,148
I-I think that I…

54
00:03:29,231 --> 00:03:31,358
[doctor] How are you feeling?

55
00:03:33,318 --> 00:03:34,445
What's wrong with her, Doctor?

56
00:03:34,528 --> 00:03:35,988
-Doctor.
-Okay.

57
00:03:37,322 --> 00:03:39,324
Now, please take a look
at this scan, dear.

58
00:03:40,034 --> 00:03:43,954
Okay. This right here indicates that
it was progressing for quite a while.

59
00:03:44,038 --> 00:03:46,665
Your condition was very, very poor.

60
00:03:46,749 --> 00:03:49,793
-You should've come in a lot sooner.
-[whimpers]

61
00:03:49,877 --> 00:03:52,671
Mr. Ga, what do I do?
I don't know what to do…

62
00:03:52,755 --> 00:03:53,797
[sighs]

63
00:03:53,881 --> 00:03:55,716
It's okay. I'm sure it's nothing serious.

64
00:03:55,799 --> 00:03:58,469
Mr. Ga. I don't want to die.

65
00:03:58,552 --> 00:04:00,387
-It's all right. Don't cry, okay?
-What do I do?

66
00:04:00,471 --> 00:04:02,389
-You're gonna be okay.
-Please call my mom for me.

67
00:04:02,473 --> 00:04:04,516
[Woo-su] If you get treated,
you'll be fine!

68
00:04:06,351 --> 00:04:09,521
My mom, I want to see my mom.

69
00:04:10,355 --> 00:04:11,774
Is it really serious?

70
00:04:12,357 --> 00:04:13,442
It's constipation.

71
00:04:19,114 --> 00:04:20,282
Huh?

72
00:04:22,326 --> 00:04:23,786
[stammering] I don't understand.

73
00:04:24,453 --> 00:04:27,539
Can someone be constipated enough
to pass out?

74
00:04:27,623 --> 00:04:29,041
Wouldn't she need some more tests?

75
00:04:29,124 --> 00:04:30,834
It was completely packed inside.

76
00:04:30,918 --> 00:04:34,213
Everything white you see in here is stool.

77
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:38,592
We gave her an enema.

78
00:04:38,675 --> 00:04:41,220
And this is how it looks now.

79
00:04:41,303 --> 00:04:43,305
All cleared up. You see?

80
00:04:45,808 --> 00:04:48,143
Oh. And once you get home,

81
00:04:48,227 --> 00:04:49,853
you should weigh yourself too.

82
00:04:51,313 --> 00:04:52,981
You're good to leave now.

83
00:05:04,451 --> 00:05:06,203
[whimpers]

84
00:05:07,913 --> 00:05:09,998
Mr. Ga, you can just leave without me.

85
00:05:10,582 --> 00:05:12,584
I can… I can go back home on my own.

86
00:05:12,668 --> 00:05:15,254
Please don't say anything and just leave.

87
00:05:15,337 --> 00:05:16,338
Please.

88
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:19,591
Oh, why aren't you leaving?

89
00:05:19,675 --> 00:05:22,511
Hurry up and leave. Please go.

90
00:05:23,095 --> 00:05:24,096
Please go.

91
00:05:25,097 --> 00:05:26,181
I don't understand.

92
00:05:28,225 --> 00:05:29,268
How do you

93
00:05:30,352 --> 00:05:31,645
always…

94
00:05:34,064 --> 00:05:36,275
How do you always manage to disappoint?

95
00:05:43,699 --> 00:05:44,700
Goodbye.

96
00:05:57,671 --> 00:05:59,089
[whimpers]

97
00:05:59,173 --> 00:06:01,300
Should I just transfer schools?

98
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:03,844
Oh. Over there.

99
00:06:03,927 --> 00:06:06,138
-Eui-ju!
-[groaning]

100
00:06:06,221 --> 00:06:07,806
-[Shin] Eui-ju! Eui-ju!
-Where is Eui-ju?

101
00:06:07,890 --> 00:06:09,683
-Eui-ju!
-Oh, sweetheart! Oh, Eui-ju!

102
00:06:09,766 --> 00:06:11,393
-My goodness, Eui-ju! Are you okay?
-I'm fine.

103
00:06:11,476 --> 00:06:12,853
-What is it?
-I'm okay. I'm all right.

104
00:06:12,936 --> 00:06:15,439
-Mom, I want to transfer.
-Transfer?

105
00:06:18,192 --> 00:06:20,611
EPISODE 8

106
00:06:22,029 --> 00:06:23,197
-Mmm.
-[sighs]

107
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:26,366
I wonder what made him change his mind
about the shoot.

108
00:06:27,117 --> 00:06:28,744
I bet he was blackmailed.

109
00:06:28,827 --> 00:06:31,830
Yeah. You guys don't know
how scary the principal is.

110
00:06:31,914 --> 00:06:33,540
Her face changes in a second.

111
00:06:33,624 --> 00:06:35,375
But Woo-su isn't one to be blackmailed.

112
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:37,002
-You're right.
-Right.

113
00:06:37,085 --> 00:06:38,378
-Yeah.
-Right.

114
00:06:39,171 --> 00:06:41,173
[sighs] But what could
she have on him, then?

115
00:06:41,256 --> 00:06:42,257
[keypad beeping]

116
00:06:42,341 --> 00:06:44,718
-He's here. Make sure you apologize.
-[door opens]

117
00:06:44,801 --> 00:06:46,094
Fine, I will.

118
00:06:49,681 --> 00:06:51,642
You're late. You haven't had dinner yet?

119
00:06:52,434 --> 00:06:53,727
[clears throat]

120
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:55,854
I'll get you some rice. Get him some soup.

121
00:07:02,694 --> 00:07:03,862
Good job today.

122
00:07:05,155 --> 00:07:06,865
That's all, really?

123
00:07:06,949 --> 00:07:09,117
I thought you said
you had something to tell Woo-su.

124
00:07:12,454 --> 00:07:14,122
Sorry about earlier.

125
00:07:14,915 --> 00:07:16,333
What are you sorry for?

126
00:07:17,042 --> 00:07:18,627
I said sorry. Isn't that enough?

127
00:07:23,548 --> 00:07:24,925
I mean…

128
00:07:28,512 --> 00:07:29,513
[sighs]

129
00:07:30,681 --> 00:07:32,307
I'm sorry for filming you,

130
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:35,269
even though I know you hate it…

131
00:07:37,312 --> 00:07:39,481
and also for telling you to get over it.

132
00:07:44,194 --> 00:07:45,404
Then that's enough.

133
00:07:45,487 --> 00:07:46,530
Spoon?

134
00:07:46,613 --> 00:07:48,782
Oh. Right. The spoon.

135
00:07:50,117 --> 00:07:51,493
[chuckles] How cool.

136
00:07:52,577 --> 00:07:54,288
[chuckles]

137
00:07:55,789 --> 00:07:57,165
Don't you have something to say?

138
00:07:59,251 --> 00:08:01,253
I won't call you a fruit bat
for the next month.

139
00:08:01,336 --> 00:08:03,088
How about the rest of your life?

140
00:08:03,171 --> 00:08:04,965
-You wish.
-You sure can, four eyes!

141
00:08:05,048 --> 00:08:06,258
-[grunts] You fruit bat.
-What?

142
00:08:06,341 --> 00:08:08,218
-What? You heard him! Fruit bat.
-[laughs]

143
00:08:08,302 --> 00:08:09,845
He said it. Yeah.

144
00:08:09,928 --> 00:08:10,929
And he said he wouldn't!

145
00:08:11,013 --> 00:08:12,306
I didn't promise you yet.

146
00:08:12,389 --> 00:08:14,641
[both laughing]

147
00:08:14,725 --> 00:08:15,809
I'm not eating.

148
00:08:16,727 --> 00:08:18,312
-This is just stupid!
-Don't eat it, then.

149
00:08:19,104 --> 00:08:20,814
[sobs]

150
00:08:20,897 --> 00:08:22,607
[sighs]

151
00:08:22,691 --> 00:08:25,736
I thought I was finally done
embarrassing myself.

152
00:08:27,237 --> 00:08:28,655
[sobbing continues]

153
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:40,751
Eui-ju! Damn it.

154
00:08:40,834 --> 00:08:41,835
[Eui-ju] It was strong.

155
00:08:42,878 --> 00:08:44,129
It was warm

156
00:08:45,589 --> 00:08:46,590
and really cozy.

157
00:08:46,673 --> 00:08:49,134
[heartbeat thumping]

158
00:08:52,262 --> 00:08:53,597
[gasps]

159
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:54,681
Oh.

160
00:08:59,102 --> 00:09:00,562
[groans, sniffles]

161
00:09:02,981 --> 00:09:03,982
[sighs]

162
00:09:29,007 --> 00:09:30,592
The current state of constipation.

163
00:09:32,135 --> 00:09:34,638
According to research
amongst high school students,

164
00:09:35,222 --> 00:09:38,183
and the study of respective causes,
the top three factors are:

165
00:09:38,266 --> 00:09:42,229
lack of exercise at 43%,
fast food at 24.6%,

166
00:09:42,312 --> 00:09:43,939
and irregular sleep at 16%.

167
00:09:44,022 --> 00:09:46,024
I believe we ended up
with yesterday's disaster

168
00:09:46,108 --> 00:09:48,276
because you dismissed every single one.

169
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,070
I'll keep that in mind.

170
00:09:50,153 --> 00:09:51,530
And thank you for yesterday.

171
00:09:51,613 --> 00:09:53,698
I'm not religious or anything like that.

172
00:09:54,282 --> 00:09:57,411
But it felt weird, showing you mercy
when you stabbed me in the back.

173
00:10:05,794 --> 00:10:08,380
How constipated were you that
you had to go to the ER?

174
00:10:09,172 --> 00:10:10,841
That's because
you didn't drink enough water.

175
00:10:10,924 --> 00:10:13,176
Your poop was so hard that
it was stuck in there.

176
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:14,678
[stammers] No, that's not true.

177
00:10:14,761 --> 00:10:15,971
[Yoon] Are you okay, Eui-ju?

178
00:10:16,054 --> 00:10:17,889
I heard you had to go to the ER.

179
00:10:18,974 --> 00:10:22,644
[sighs] I can't believe you let it stay
in there until it became that bad.

180
00:10:23,562 --> 00:10:25,230
-You're definitely a bit slow.
-Uh…

181
00:10:25,772 --> 00:10:28,483
-Ah. Good job yesterday.
-Wait, Mr. Noh.

182
00:10:30,652 --> 00:10:33,530
What was that yesterday?
You said you knew about it.

183
00:10:34,781 --> 00:10:35,907
Knew what?

184
00:10:36,741 --> 00:10:38,952
You said you knew all about my secret.

185
00:10:39,786 --> 00:10:40,829
I don't know anything.

186
00:10:42,164 --> 00:10:43,457
[gasps]

187
00:10:46,918 --> 00:10:49,588
Your face has really cleared up.
You look great now.

188
00:10:53,884 --> 00:10:54,885
[door closes]

189
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,721
What the…

190
00:10:58,889 --> 00:11:00,390
Did I fall for his lie?

191
00:11:01,892 --> 00:11:04,728
So, Math didn't tell him about my novel?
At all?

192
00:11:08,315 --> 00:11:12,569
Hey, Eui-ju! Going to the ER
for constipation is no big deal!

193
00:11:12,652 --> 00:11:13,945
Don't be so embarrassed!

194
00:11:14,029 --> 00:11:15,614
Hey, I wish you a clean finish!

195
00:11:15,697 --> 00:11:16,698
Good luck, Eui-ju!

196
00:11:17,282 --> 00:11:18,658
Constipation is no joke!

197
00:11:18,742 --> 00:11:20,368
Okay, I'll stop. See you!

198
00:11:27,042 --> 00:11:28,335
[sobs]

199
00:11:29,711 --> 00:11:30,837
-Oh A-rin.
-Here.

200
00:11:30,921 --> 00:11:32,297
CHAPTER 27:
LIKE A CAT, LITTLE BY LITTLE

201
00:11:32,380 --> 00:11:34,132
-Choi Yu-mi.
-Here.

202
00:11:34,216 --> 00:11:35,592
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Here.

203
00:11:36,676 --> 00:11:38,094
-Choi Go-ya.
-Here.

204
00:11:38,178 --> 00:11:39,179
Choi Ji-a.

205
00:11:50,398 --> 00:11:51,608
-Hong Su-min.
-Here.

206
00:11:52,234 --> 00:11:53,318
-Jeon Chae-won.
-Here.

207
00:11:53,401 --> 00:11:54,819
-Im Su-yeon.
-Here.

208
00:11:55,904 --> 00:11:57,197
-Jenny.
-Here.

209
00:11:58,949 --> 00:12:01,409
Have fun with your classes today.
Good luck.

210
00:12:01,493 --> 00:12:03,245
[students] Thank you.

211
00:12:03,328 --> 00:12:04,412
Yeo Eui-ju, outside.

212
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:07,040
[door opens]

213
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:10,377
[students murmuring]

214
00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:11,461
[sighs]

215
00:12:15,549 --> 00:12:16,633
Why is Choi Ji-a not here?

216
00:12:17,551 --> 00:12:19,219
I'm not really sure either.

217
00:12:19,302 --> 00:12:20,345
[sighs]

218
00:12:20,428 --> 00:12:22,430
When I asked about her
on my first day at this school,

219
00:12:22,514 --> 00:12:25,100
you were the only one who answered me.
Guess what that means.

220
00:12:26,768 --> 00:12:27,769
Right.

221
00:12:28,311 --> 00:12:30,772
I thought maybe you could help Choi Ji-a
adjust to the school,

222
00:12:30,855 --> 00:12:32,065
maybe help her change a little.

223
00:12:32,649 --> 00:12:35,443
That's the reason I talked to you
and the reason I trusted you.

224
00:12:39,072 --> 00:12:41,408
So take more interest
and try to help a out a little more.

225
00:12:41,992 --> 00:12:45,203
Imagine someone waiting for you at school,
you'll force yourself to attend.

226
00:12:45,287 --> 00:12:47,455
Even if you don't want to,
don't you think?

227
00:12:47,539 --> 00:12:48,790
[gasps]

228
00:12:48,873 --> 00:12:51,084
But Mr. Ga,

229
00:12:51,167 --> 00:12:54,379
the way I see it, it's not good
to go too fast with Ji-a.

230
00:12:54,921 --> 00:12:57,882
You need to be gentle

231
00:12:58,508 --> 00:13:02,804
and take it slow
like with a cat little by little.

232
00:13:05,682 --> 00:13:06,766
Then do that.

233
00:13:09,436 --> 00:13:10,979
-Four demerit points today.
-[gasps]

234
00:13:11,896 --> 00:13:13,940
Will you betray my trust again?

235
00:13:14,024 --> 00:13:15,108
I won't, Mr. Ga.

236
00:13:23,408 --> 00:13:25,744
[sighs, mumbling]

237
00:13:26,620 --> 00:13:27,621
[grunts]

238
00:13:29,039 --> 00:13:30,957
Darn Choi Ji-a.

239
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:33,918
Ji-a's not here again.

240
00:13:34,002 --> 00:13:35,253
I know.

241
00:13:36,171 --> 00:13:39,257
And do you know why she's always alone?

242
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:41,760
I don't know.

243
00:13:41,843 --> 00:13:46,222
Well, some people find it more comfortable
to be alone. Maybe she's like that.

244
00:13:46,306 --> 00:13:51,353
Mmm… Honestly, Ji-a is a bit scary.

245
00:13:51,436 --> 00:13:53,855
If I rub her the wrong way,
she might blow up.

246
00:13:54,481 --> 00:13:55,482
[chuckles]

247
00:13:55,565 --> 00:13:58,610
Nah. She's not that scary.
She's just quiet.

248
00:13:58,693 --> 00:14:00,862
She was in my class
in our first year of high school.

249
00:14:00,945 --> 00:14:04,240
Whenever there was chalk on the floor,
she would put it right back on the board.

250
00:14:04,324 --> 00:14:07,160
Oh, and while everyone else hated
taking out the recycled waste,

251
00:14:07,243 --> 00:14:10,080
she'd stay until the very end
to finish it all by herself.

252
00:14:10,163 --> 00:14:12,749
-Mmm…
-So then… [sharply inhales]

253
00:14:12,832 --> 00:14:15,460
…her actions speak louder than her words.

254
00:14:15,543 --> 00:14:16,961
I think that's just her style.

255
00:14:17,045 --> 00:14:18,171
Mm-hmm.

256
00:14:18,254 --> 00:14:19,255
Ji-a's here.

257
00:14:20,215 --> 00:14:21,216
Oh.

258
00:14:22,759 --> 00:14:23,760
You're here.

259
00:14:24,886 --> 00:14:26,262
You should've been on time.

260
00:14:27,472 --> 00:14:29,265
Why were you late today, Ji-a?

261
00:14:32,686 --> 00:14:33,687
[Jenny] Mmm…

262
00:14:46,991 --> 00:14:48,326
[bell rings]

263
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:51,204
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

264
00:14:52,831 --> 00:14:54,541
-Hi.
-[students] Hello.

265
00:14:59,003 --> 00:15:01,131
All right, turn to page 280.

266
00:15:01,214 --> 00:15:03,049
[students] Okay.

267
00:15:05,635 --> 00:15:06,636
Oh.

268
00:15:07,345 --> 00:15:08,346
Everyone.

269
00:15:08,430 --> 00:15:12,308
We'll be holding a poetry and art
exhibition to celebrate Literature Month.

270
00:15:12,392 --> 00:15:14,310
Each class needs
to pick one representative.

271
00:15:14,394 --> 00:15:16,938
Is there anyone who wants to write a poem?

272
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,569
Mr. Yoon! Eui-ju.

273
00:15:22,652 --> 00:15:23,903
She's really good at writing.

274
00:15:24,487 --> 00:15:26,072
Right, she always doodles in her notebook.

275
00:15:26,156 --> 00:15:28,116
She even won a contest last year.

276
00:15:28,658 --> 00:15:30,910
-[students] Ooh.
-[chuckles]

277
00:15:31,411 --> 00:15:35,457
Oh, really? In that case, it'll be nice
if Eui-ju can be the class representative.

278
00:15:35,540 --> 00:15:36,958
What do you say, Eui-ju?

279
00:15:37,709 --> 00:15:40,003
Sure. I'll give it a try.

280
00:15:40,086 --> 00:15:41,963
Mr. Yoon. Can Go-ya do the drawings?

281
00:15:42,046 --> 00:15:43,256
Yeah, sounds great.

282
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,508
So, Go-ya. Can you do it?

283
00:15:47,051 --> 00:15:49,637
Yes. Anything I can do to help.

284
00:15:50,305 --> 00:15:53,224
Okay then. You both are
the representatives for Class 2.

285
00:15:53,308 --> 00:15:54,809
[both giggle]

286
00:15:55,643 --> 00:15:56,770
I'm excited.

287
00:15:56,853 --> 00:15:58,980
-Okay. We'll do our best.
-Okay.

288
00:15:59,063 --> 00:16:01,065
[giggling]

289
00:16:12,786 --> 00:16:14,662
Are you cleaning because of your demerits?

290
00:16:14,746 --> 00:16:16,706
Uh… [chuckles] Yes.

291
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:20,585
I don't know when I'll get more
so I need to cross them out while I can.

292
00:16:21,961 --> 00:16:23,004
Did you have lunch already?

293
00:16:23,671 --> 00:16:24,672
Yes, did you?

294
00:16:24,756 --> 00:16:25,757
I did.

295
00:16:28,176 --> 00:16:29,177
Eui-ju.

296
00:16:29,260 --> 00:16:30,261
Yes?

297
00:16:36,351 --> 00:16:39,854
Mr. Ga knows that you weren't filming
when you were out with your phone

298
00:16:39,938 --> 00:16:41,439
when we first met.

299
00:16:41,523 --> 00:16:42,524
Really?

300
00:16:42,607 --> 00:16:43,858
Mmm.

301
00:16:44,442 --> 00:16:46,444
Then why is he always picking on me?

302
00:16:48,029 --> 00:16:49,030
Oh.

303
00:16:50,615 --> 00:16:52,617
It's because of the glasses.

304
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:53,701
The glasses?

305
00:16:53,785 --> 00:16:55,119
[sighs]

306
00:16:55,203 --> 00:16:56,955
Yes. His glasses.

307
00:16:57,038 --> 00:16:59,833
I was the one who had them
when he couldn't find them anywhere.

308
00:17:00,416 --> 00:17:02,585
You were the one who had his glasses?

309
00:17:03,878 --> 00:17:04,879
Yes.

310
00:17:06,047 --> 00:17:07,340
Didn't Mr. Ga tell you?

311
00:17:07,924 --> 00:17:09,133
He didn't say a word about it.

312
00:17:10,176 --> 00:17:11,427
[Eui-ju] What the…

313
00:17:11,511 --> 00:17:15,181
He didn't talk crap about me
for throwing his glasses away?

314
00:17:15,265 --> 00:17:19,269
Anyway, he's not like that
because he has hard feelings against you.

315
00:17:19,352 --> 00:17:20,353
So don't get too upset.

316
00:17:20,436 --> 00:17:23,231
[chuckles] Okay.
Thank you so much for your concern.

317
00:17:23,898 --> 00:17:28,027
Oh. By the way, it's truly incredible that
you made your literary debut.

318
00:17:28,111 --> 00:17:29,863
Nah, it's nothing.

319
00:17:29,946 --> 00:17:32,657
I've just enjoyed writing poetry
since I was little.

320
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:35,201
At first,
it was simply like writing a journal.

321
00:17:36,119 --> 00:17:40,039
The emotions that were too heavy
to keep inside, I let out in my writing.

322
00:17:42,041 --> 00:17:45,378
After failing the New Spring
Literary Contest so much,

323
00:17:45,461 --> 00:17:48,006
I got lucky one day,
and was selected by a magazine.

324
00:17:48,590 --> 00:17:51,384
Of course, I still kept doubting myself.

325
00:17:52,302 --> 00:17:54,095
Was it the correct way to write?

326
00:17:55,054 --> 00:17:57,265
But then, I kept writing.

327
00:17:57,348 --> 00:18:01,519
And then I realized
it was about putting your heart into it.

328
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:07,233
Yeah. Actually,

329
00:18:07,984 --> 00:18:11,279
I've been sort of writing novels as well.

330
00:18:11,946 --> 00:18:12,989
Seriously?

331
00:18:13,865 --> 00:18:14,866
That's cool.

332
00:18:14,949 --> 00:18:15,950
Not at all.

333
00:18:16,034 --> 00:18:17,035
[chuckles]

334
00:18:17,994 --> 00:18:22,373
Sir, what should I do to be really good
at writing novels?

335
00:18:25,043 --> 00:18:26,252
[sighs]

336
00:18:29,881 --> 00:18:33,551
Every single character has to have
a voice of their own.

337
00:18:35,511 --> 00:18:36,804
I think that's important.

338
00:18:39,182 --> 00:18:43,603
Every single character has to have
a voice of their own…

339
00:18:45,563 --> 00:18:47,231
-Right.
-Oh.

340
00:18:47,315 --> 00:18:50,234
-Wow, Mr. Yoon. That's cool.
-[both chuckle]

341
00:18:51,945 --> 00:18:53,613
I can't wait to read your piece
for the exhibition.

342
00:18:53,696 --> 00:18:54,530
Ah…

343
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:23,643
You went to the store?

344
00:19:25,395 --> 00:19:26,521
Yeah.

345
00:19:26,604 --> 00:19:28,064
You should've come with me.

346
00:19:28,147 --> 00:19:29,148
Thank you.

347
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:31,234
What did you do?

348
00:19:31,943 --> 00:19:34,821
Huh? Ah, I had a talk with Mr. Yoon.

349
00:19:34,904 --> 00:19:37,532
[sighs] Hey. He's really cool, you know?

350
00:19:37,615 --> 00:19:40,326
Apparently, he wrote poetry
since he was in middle school.

351
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:43,037
He failed a known Literary Contest
until he made a debut

352
00:19:43,121 --> 00:19:45,832
through a different route
unrelated to the contest.

353
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:49,836
You know what? I'll write something
really good for the exhibit.

354
00:19:49,919 --> 00:19:52,797
That way your amazing drawings
will stand out even more.

355
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,590
Let's show everyone
your beautiful drawings…

356
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,510
[sighs] …and how fantastic they are.

357
00:19:57,593 --> 00:19:59,137
Oh, I'm nervous.

358
00:20:00,596 --> 00:20:01,597
[slurps]

359
00:20:02,223 --> 00:20:03,307
Mmm.

360
00:20:03,391 --> 00:20:05,018
Should I start with the title?

361
00:20:05,101 --> 00:20:06,811
Wait, no. [inhales sharply]

362
00:20:06,894 --> 00:20:10,314
CHAPTER 28: I'M GOING TO TRY
TO UNDERSTAND IRRATIONAL NUMBERS

363
00:20:13,109 --> 00:20:15,319
FILES FOR MR. GA
REAL FILES

364
00:20:15,403 --> 00:20:16,779
[sighs]

365
00:20:18,072 --> 00:20:19,782
[smacks lips] Right.

366
00:20:19,866 --> 00:20:20,825
FILES FOR MR. GA

367
00:20:20,908 --> 00:20:22,910
[sighs]

368
00:20:23,703 --> 00:20:26,039
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

369
00:20:27,957 --> 00:20:29,167
[groans]

370
00:20:35,923 --> 00:20:37,550
[sighs]

371
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:39,343
[whimpers, groans]

372
00:20:41,137 --> 00:20:42,138
WOO-SUUUUUUUU

373
00:20:44,098 --> 00:20:45,349
[sighs] No.

374
00:20:46,184 --> 00:20:48,394
Just skip it. [sighs] No.

375
00:20:48,478 --> 00:20:50,104
[clicks tongue] I'll come back to it.

376
00:20:51,147 --> 00:20:52,273
No. No.

377
00:20:52,356 --> 00:20:53,524
REAL FILES

378
00:20:58,237 --> 00:20:59,572
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

379
00:21:01,699 --> 00:21:04,452
[inhales deeply] Hmm.

380
00:21:04,535 --> 00:21:06,454
[western music playing]

381
00:21:06,537 --> 00:21:08,081
JUST THEN, SOMEONE GRABBED…

382
00:21:11,501 --> 00:21:14,670
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

383
00:21:15,671 --> 00:21:17,131
Why aren't you coming to my house?

384
00:21:17,799 --> 00:21:19,300
YOON'S EYES WIDEN IN SURPRISE.
IT'S SI-ON

385
00:21:20,051 --> 00:21:21,177
I can't go there anymore.

386
00:21:21,260 --> 00:21:23,221
Actually, I won't.

387
00:21:23,304 --> 00:21:25,556
You can't handle Discrete Math without me!

388
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,517
If I don't teach you,
you're just gonna fail.

389
00:21:29,268 --> 00:21:30,770
I'll be fine.

390
00:21:31,479 --> 00:21:32,480
I'll pay you.

391
00:21:35,274 --> 00:21:36,275
What?

392
00:21:36,359 --> 00:21:37,652
I know you need money.

393
00:21:38,319 --> 00:21:39,987
I'll pay you if you come to my house.

394
00:21:41,155 --> 00:21:43,574
Isn't that why
you go to Kang Tae-ha's house?

395
00:21:43,658 --> 00:21:44,659
No, that's not it.

396
00:21:45,243 --> 00:21:46,369
Yes, it is.

397
00:21:46,452 --> 00:21:48,079
How am I any different from that punk?

398
00:21:48,162 --> 00:21:49,497
Well, he just is.

399
00:21:50,832 --> 00:21:52,667
He's different? How so?

400
00:21:53,668 --> 00:21:56,587
In the end, he's still trying to buy you
with money. Isn't it the same?

401
00:21:57,839 --> 00:21:59,757
[Tae-ha] Since you're poor,
you'll have to compensate me

402
00:21:59,841 --> 00:22:01,425
with something other than money.

403
00:22:01,509 --> 00:22:02,635
Six thousand.

404
00:22:03,511 --> 00:22:05,388
I'll watch how you repay all of it.

405
00:22:07,723 --> 00:22:08,850
[scoffs]

406
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:10,017
Fine, go ahead.

407
00:22:10,643 --> 00:22:12,436
Get mad while you keep your pride.

408
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,647
You're gonna take the money anyway, right?

409
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:17,358
I'm curious.
How much is your pride really worth?

410
00:22:18,776 --> 00:22:20,570
Why do you take it this far?

411
00:22:21,237 --> 00:22:23,447
Why do you have to make me feel
this miserable?

412
00:22:24,448 --> 00:22:25,700
Do I look that easy to you?

413
00:22:25,783 --> 00:22:27,994
Don't waste your time.
Just think of a number.

414
00:22:29,537 --> 00:22:31,873
Listen. You're going to regret it.

415
00:22:32,748 --> 00:22:34,625
You're definitely going to regret it.

416
00:22:34,709 --> 00:22:35,793
Oh, no.

417
00:22:36,377 --> 00:22:37,628
I'll never regret it.

418
00:22:37,712 --> 00:22:39,130
Not even if I die.

419
00:22:41,424 --> 00:22:42,884
END OF EPISODE 5

420
00:22:46,888 --> 00:22:48,014
[Eui-ju] "Save."

421
00:22:52,143 --> 00:22:53,144
[sighs]

422
00:22:53,227 --> 00:22:54,061
FILES FOR MR. GA

423
00:22:57,356 --> 00:22:58,482
[sighs]

424
00:22:59,984 --> 00:23:01,027
You can do this.

425
00:23:01,861 --> 00:23:02,862
Eui-ju.

426
00:23:03,613 --> 00:23:05,072
You can do it. [grunts]

427
00:23:05,615 --> 00:23:07,158
I couldn't stop yawning.

428
00:23:07,241 --> 00:23:08,659
I need to go to bed.

429
00:23:08,743 --> 00:23:09,869
Right after dinner.

430
00:23:10,494 --> 00:23:11,871
What are we having?

431
00:23:11,954 --> 00:23:13,998
Uh… I don't know.

432
00:23:14,081 --> 00:23:15,666
Something really crispy and warm.

433
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:17,752
-Ah… This jerk is way too picky.
-[Da-ju] Crispy!

434
00:23:17,835 --> 00:23:19,212
Hey, we have some curry left.

435
00:23:19,295 --> 00:23:20,630
-Curry?
-Yes. We have some left.

436
00:23:20,713 --> 00:23:21,547
Go without me.

437
00:23:23,216 --> 00:23:25,009
-Where are you going?
-The library.

438
00:23:26,135 --> 00:23:27,345
He goes to the library a lot.

439
00:23:27,887 --> 00:23:29,222
Hey, don't be late for dinner!

440
00:23:31,933 --> 00:23:34,936
[Dong-ju] Is there anything in the library
worth reading for Woo-su, though?

441
00:23:36,354 --> 00:23:37,563
[door opens]

442
00:23:42,985 --> 00:23:44,820
[footsteps approaching]

443
00:24:06,759 --> 00:24:08,302
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

444
00:24:14,517 --> 00:24:15,893
[Si-on] From now on,

445
00:24:15,977 --> 00:24:17,853
I'm gonna be a piece of work,
just for Choi Yoon.

446
00:24:19,397 --> 00:24:20,439
This isn't like you.

447
00:24:20,523 --> 00:24:21,524
No?

448
00:24:21,607 --> 00:24:22,483
EPISODE 5, FOR MR. GA

449
00:24:22,566 --> 00:24:23,401
Then what is, huh?

450
00:24:23,484 --> 00:24:25,236
I know you didn't even like me.

451
00:24:25,319 --> 00:24:28,823
You're suddenly doing this
because I got close with Tae-ha.

452
00:24:29,490 --> 00:24:31,659
Is that it? Are you jealous now?

453
00:24:32,410 --> 00:24:33,411
Jealous?

454
00:24:34,245 --> 00:24:35,705
You think I'm actually jealous?

455
00:24:35,788 --> 00:24:37,081
[scoffs, laughs]

456
00:24:38,541 --> 00:24:40,543
[funky music playing]

457
00:24:40,626 --> 00:24:41,460
That's right, I am.

458
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:45,631
The way I treated you was all an act.
I didn't want you to see my true feelings.

459
00:24:46,215 --> 00:24:49,135
But seeing Tae-ha by your side,
it drove me crazy.

460
00:24:49,927 --> 00:24:51,304
[Yoon] It's no use now.

461
00:24:52,305 --> 00:24:53,597
Snap out of it, Yoon!

462
00:24:54,974 --> 00:24:57,226
You've got no one, but me.

463
00:24:58,060 --> 00:24:59,270
There's no other choice.

464
00:24:59,353 --> 00:25:02,273
Without me, you've got nothing.
You know that!

465
00:25:09,322 --> 00:25:10,948
END OF EPISODE 5

466
00:25:21,417 --> 00:25:22,793
What is it, Mr. Ga?

467
00:25:23,836 --> 00:25:25,296
Do you not like it?

468
00:25:27,048 --> 00:25:28,341
[sighs]

469
00:25:35,014 --> 00:25:36,015
Huh?

470
00:25:36,849 --> 00:25:38,434
[sighs] What was that?

471
00:25:50,446 --> 00:25:52,907
I made him look like
a total obsessive guy.

472
00:25:52,990 --> 00:25:54,408
What is he unhappy about?

473
00:26:10,257 --> 00:26:13,302
Oh, boy.
There's still tape around his glasses.

474
00:26:15,471 --> 00:26:16,472
What is it?

475
00:26:18,474 --> 00:26:21,936
I'm just wondering
if you aren't going to get new glasses.

476
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:23,938
I ordered a new pair already.

477
00:26:25,481 --> 00:26:26,732
I bet they're expensive.

478
00:26:27,274 --> 00:26:29,819
I know I can't pay for your new glasses.
I'm sorry.

479
00:26:30,861 --> 00:26:31,862
You're sorry, right?

480
00:26:32,863 --> 00:26:33,864
Of course.

481
00:26:35,741 --> 00:26:37,410
Is that your excuse for giving up on math?

482
00:26:40,121 --> 00:26:41,372
Yes.

483
00:26:49,755 --> 00:26:51,382
Write it the way you want to then.

484
00:26:53,509 --> 00:26:54,510
What?

485
00:26:55,344 --> 00:26:57,596
You can stick to your version,
instead of doing mine.

486
00:26:58,639 --> 00:26:59,974
Are you serious?

487
00:27:00,057 --> 00:27:01,976
No way. Can I really do that?

488
00:27:08,399 --> 00:27:09,400
[sniffles]

489
00:27:10,401 --> 00:27:13,154
Honestly, after you caught me
writing back then,

490
00:27:13,237 --> 00:27:15,156
I actually thought it was all over.

491
00:27:15,656 --> 00:27:17,491
I figured
I'd never be able to write again.

492
00:27:19,076 --> 00:27:22,913
So, why are you even
letting me keep writing it?

493
00:27:33,382 --> 00:27:36,385
To Pythagoras,
root two was something abnormal.

494
00:27:37,970 --> 00:27:38,929
Huh?

495
00:27:40,139 --> 00:27:41,265
That's random.

496
00:27:41,348 --> 00:27:44,685
In those days, only natural numbers
were thought to be computable.

497
00:27:44,768 --> 00:27:47,980
Anything that couldn't be expressed
as a fraction was considered irrational

498
00:27:48,063 --> 00:27:51,066
and to be rejected.
It was an idea that shouldn't even exist.

499
00:27:52,443 --> 00:27:54,445
Do you know what happened
to the Pythagoreans?

500
00:27:55,029 --> 00:27:58,491
In the end, a student named Hippasus,
who discovered root two,

501
00:27:58,574 --> 00:27:59,658
met a mysterious death.

502
00:28:00,951 --> 00:28:02,828
They killed him because of that?

503
00:28:05,247 --> 00:28:07,541
It's unclear who killed him.
It's just a rumor.

504
00:28:08,125 --> 00:28:11,253
Dang. I guess Pythagoras
was a really scary man.

505
00:28:15,758 --> 00:28:16,884
Irrational number.

506
00:28:18,886 --> 00:28:20,346
Irrational number, right?

507
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:25,351
I believe it's worth embracing that which
isn't rational or logical for that matter.

508
00:28:25,434 --> 00:28:28,062
I won't fall into the same trap
as Pythagoras

509
00:28:28,145 --> 00:28:30,856
who rejected root two
because it didn't fit his logic.

510
00:28:33,526 --> 00:28:35,486
Couldn't you make it a bit simpler?

511
00:28:42,701 --> 00:28:44,662
I want to understand irrational numbers.

512
00:28:45,371 --> 00:28:47,373
[light pop music playing]

513
00:29:17,987 --> 00:29:20,614
[Eui-ju]
Fangirling used to be my only joy in life.

514
00:29:20,698 --> 00:29:22,575
-Are you okay?
-But now,

515
00:29:22,658 --> 00:29:24,493
every time he crosses my mind.

516
00:29:24,577 --> 00:29:25,578
[grunts] I get so mad!

517
00:29:25,661 --> 00:29:27,538
-I really don't want to think about him.
-Let's go.

518
00:29:27,621 --> 00:29:29,707
I'm not supposed to think about him.

519
00:29:29,790 --> 00:29:31,166
But he's stuck in my head.

520
00:29:31,250 --> 00:29:34,003
[Go-ya] You're already head over heels
for him. But you're trying to deny it.

521
00:29:34,086 --> 00:29:35,170
That's just typical.

522
00:29:35,254 --> 00:29:38,299
Your words say otherwise, but your heart
is already racing toward him.

523
00:29:38,382 --> 00:29:40,676
[Eui-ju] No! What? Oh, no.

524
00:29:40,759 --> 00:29:42,219
I can't. I shouldn't like him.

525
00:29:42,303 --> 00:29:43,429
I simply can't!

526
00:29:44,013 --> 00:29:46,682
[Go-ya] Hey.
Mr. Jung's not your crush, is he?

527
00:29:47,516 --> 00:29:49,226
They've gotten really close.
